National Charter Schools Institute
April 23 at 2:00 PM ·

We want to kick off our #schoolbrag campaign with a submission by AppleTree Early Learning Public Charter School in Washington DC! @AppleTreeInst developed a partnership with the Smithsonian Early Enrichment Center to provide exclusive museum access and Smithsonian-guided workshops for the students and their families.

Very cool and thanks for sharing!

Send your #schoolbrag to media@charterinstitute.org so we can highlight your students, teachers and faculty!

#washingtondc #schools #education #smithsonian #museums #teachers #students #families

post_text:
FREE Online Course for Early Childhood Educators!
AppleTree Institute is offering a free, self-paced online course for early childhood educators and instructional leaders! Click here to register: https://lnkd.in/dix92Gp

The Questions, Questions, Questions online course explores using varied questions as strategies to support higher-order thinking and differentiated instruction. Learners will also receive a visual question taxonomy designed for early educators to use in their classrooms. If you’d like to learn more, visit the Questions, Questions, Questions registration page.

Registration: March 11-March 26, 2020
Course Availability: April 1 - May 1, 2020
Contact AppleTree Institute at aiq.facilitator@appletreeinstitute.org with questions.
